Advanced Voice Butler: Google Integration Guide (Updated)

This comprehensive guide details the technical configuration required to bridge the Advanced Voice Butler ecosystem with Google Workspace. By utilizing a serverless Google Apps Script, the system achieves zero-polling, real-time synchronization for calendar events, priority email routing, package tracking, and Ooma voicemail transcriptions.

Phase 1: Hubitat Cloud Endpoint Preparation
Before configuring the external script, the Hubitat environment must be authorized to receive secure inbound webhooks.

Navigate to the Apps Code section within the Hubitat administrative interface and select the Advanced Voice Butler application.

Locate and engage the OAuth configuration protocol.

Select Enable OAuth in App. There is no requirement to define redirect URIs for this specific implementation.

Commit the changes by selecting Update.

Access the active Voice Butler application instance via the main Apps menu. Navigate to the Live System Dashboard to retrieve the newly generated Cloud Webhook URL. Copy the base URL (excluding the specific endpoint paths like /email or /calendar) for use in Phase 3.

Phase 2: Gmail Filter and Search Parameters
The Voice Butler's Master Wrapper is pre-configured with algorithmic search strings to isolate specific types of communications automatically.

Package Deliveries: The script automatically scans for subject lines containing "out for delivery", "package arriving", or "scheduled for delivery".

Ooma Voicemails: The script automatically targets emails specifically from notify@ooma.com with the subject "New Voicemail".

Important Emails: By default, the script looks for is:unread is:important. If you prefer absolute precision and wish to avoid algorithmic false positives, you can create a custom label (e.g., Butler-Alert) and update the script's search string to is:unread label:Butler-Alert.

Phase 3: Google Apps Script Deployment
The serverless function acts as the intermediary, securely pushing verified events from the Google ecosystem directly into the Hubitat TTS queue. The updated architecture utilizes a "Master Wrapper" to process all services in a single execution, significantly lowering your Google CPU usage.

Access the Google Apps Script portal at script.google.com and initialize a New Project.

Clear the default workspace and inject the following JavaScript payload. Ensure the HUBITAT_BASE_URL constant is updated with the secure endpoint retrieved during Phase 1.

// --- ADVANCED VOICE BUTLER BRIDGE ---
// Your secure Hubitat Cloud API Endpoint
const HUBITAT_BASE_URL = "YOUR_SECURE_HUBITAT_CLOUD_URL_HERE"; 

// This is the MASTER function. Set your 5-minute Time-Driven trigger to run THIS function only!
function checkImportantEmails() {
  // Look for unread emails labeled "important" (Change to 'is:unread label:Butler-Alert' if using custom labels)
  const threads = GmailApp.search('is:unread is:important', 0, 1);
  
  if (threads.length > 0) {
    const message = threads[0].getMessages()[0];
    
    const payload = {
      sender: message.getFrom(),
      subject: message.getSubject(),
      snippet: message.getPlainBody().substring(0, 150) + "..." // Read the first 150 characters
    };
    
    const options = {
      method: 'post',
      contentType: 'application/json',
      payload: JSON.stringify(payload)
    };
    
    // Inject the /email path into your URL and send to Hubitat
    UrlFetchApp.fetch(HUBITAT_BASE_URL.replace("?", "/email?"), options);
    
    // Mark as read so the Butler doesn't repeat it on the next loop
    message.markRead(); 
  }
  
  // Instantly check for voicemails, deliveries, and calendar updates right after checking emails
  checkOomaVoicemails();
  checkDeliveryEmails();
  pushCalendarUpdates();
}

function checkOomaVoicemails() {
  // Searches for unread Ooma notifications
  const threads = GmailApp.search('is:unread from:notify@ooma.com subject:"New Voicemail"', 0, 1);
  
  if (threads.length > 0) {
    const message = threads[0].getMessages()[0];
    const subject = message.getSubject();
    const body = message.getPlainBody();
    
    // Ooma subjects usually look like: New Voicemail from NAME (555-555-5555)
    // We strip "New Voicemail from" to just get the caller
    const caller = subject.replace("New Voicemail from", "").trim();
    
    // Attempt to grab the transcription (usually starts after "Message:")
    let transcription = "No transcription available.";
    if (body.includes("Message:")) {
      transcription = body.split("Message:")[1].split("To listen to")[0].trim();
    }

    const payload = {
      isVoicemail: true,
      sender: caller,
      msgContent: transcription,
      time: Utilities.formatDate(message.getDate(), "GMT-5", "h:mm a") // Adjust for your timezone
    };
    
    const options = {
      method: 'post',
      contentType: 'application/json',
      payload: JSON.stringify(payload)
    };
    
    UrlFetchApp.fetch(HUBITAT_BASE_URL.replace("?", "/email?"), options);
    message.markRead(); 
  }
}

function checkDeliveryEmails() {
  // Looks for common delivery phrases. Adjust keywords as needed!
  const threads = GmailApp.search('is:unread (subject:"out for delivery" OR subject:"package arriving" OR subject:"scheduled for delivery")', 0, 1);
  
  if (threads.length > 0) {
    const message = threads[0].getMessages()[0];
    const payload = {
      isDelivery: true, // This flag triggers the specific Butler package phrasing
      sender: message.getFrom(),
      subject: message.getSubject()
    };
    
    const options = {
      method: 'post',
      contentType: 'application/json',
      payload: JSON.stringify(payload)
    };
    
    UrlFetchApp.fetch(HUBITAT_BASE_URL.replace("?", "/email?"), options);
    message.markRead(); 
  }
}

function pushCalendarUpdates() {
  const now = new Date();
  // Look 5 days ahead
  const events = CalendarApp.getDefaultCalendar().getEvents(now, new Date(now.getTime() + (5 * 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000)));
  
  let upcoming = [];
  for (let i = 0; i < events.length; i++) {
    let evt = events[i];
    
    // 1. Bypass the "All-Day" Trap (Ignores things like holidays taking up the #1 slot)
    if (evt.isAllDayEvent()) continue;
    
    // 2. Bypass the "Ongoing Event" Trap (Ignores events that already started)
    let startTime = evt.getStartTime().getTime();
    if (startTime <= now.getTime()) continue;
    
    // Build the array of valid upcoming events
    upcoming.push({
      title: evt.getTitle(),
      epoch: startTime
    });
    
    // 3. Keep a maximum of 5 upcoming events in the queue
    if (upcoming.length >= 5) break;
  }
  
  const options = {
    method: 'post',
    contentType: 'application/json',
    payload: JSON.stringify({ events: upcoming })
  };
  
  // Inject the /calendar path and send the array to Hubitat
  UrlFetchApp.fetch(HUBITAT_BASE_URL.replace("?", "/calendar?"), options);
}


